{{Navigate|Book=Grsecurity/Appendix|Curr=Role Modes|Prev=Grsecurity and PaX Configuration Options|Next=Role Attributes}}
{| style="border-collapse:collapse;border-bottom:3px solid #999;" cellpadding="3px" width=100% |-style="background:#666;color:white;" ! width=60px style="border:1px solid gray;" |Mode ! style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:left;" |Meaning |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''u''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This role is a user role. That is, the role name must be an existing user on the system. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''g''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This role is a group role. That is, the role name must be an existing group on the system. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''s''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This role is a special role, meaning it does not belong to a user or group and does not require an enforced secure policy base to be included in the ruleset. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''l''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Lowercase L. This role has learning enabled. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''A''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This role is an administrative role, thus it has special privileges that normal roles do not have. In particular, this role bypasses the additional ptrace and library loading restrictions. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''G''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This role can use <tt>gradm</tt> to authenticate to the kernel. A policy for <tt>gradm</tt> will automatically be added to the role. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''N''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This role does not require authentication. To access this role, use '<tt>gradm -n <rolename></tt>'. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''P''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This role uses [[w:Pluggable_Authentication_Modules|Pluggable Authentication Modules]] (PAM) for authentication. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''T''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This role has Trusted Path Execution (TPE) enabled. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''R''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|The role is persistence. When shell/session in which authorization was done is terminated, spawned processes won't be dropped to non-special role. Do '''NOT''' use this flag with any role that does anything but shut the system down. |}
{{auto navigation|Role Attributes|Grsecurity and PaX Configuration Options}}
