{{Navigate|Book=Grsecurity/Appendix|Curr=Object Modes|Next=PaX Flags|Prev=Subject Attributes}}
{| style="border-collapse:collapse;border-bottom:3px solid #999;" cellpadding="3px" width=100% |-style="background:#666;color:white;" ! width=60px style="border:1px solid gray;" |Mode ! style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:left;" |Meaning |- |+ Object Permission Modes | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''none''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Lack of any of the below modes implies "find" access to the object. The object can be listed and have its ownership, size, etc. information obtained, but cannot be read or modified. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''a''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This object can be opened for appending. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''c''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Allow creation of the file/directory. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''d''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Allow deletion of the file/directory. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''f''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Needed to mark the pipe used for communication with init to transfer the privilege of the persistent role; only valid within a persistent role. Transfer only occurs when the file is opened for writing. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''h''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This object is hidden. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''i''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This mode only applies to binaries. When the object is executed, it inherits the ACL of the subject in which it was contained. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''l''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Lowercase L. Allow a hardlink at this path. Hardlinking requires a minimum of c and l modes, and the target link cannot have any greater permission than the source file. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''m''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Allow creation of setuid/setgid files/directories and modification of files/directories to be setuid/setgid. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''p''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Reject all ptraces to this object. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''r''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This object can be opened for reading. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''t''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This object can be ptraced, but cannot modify the running task. This is referred to as a 'read-only ptrace'. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''w''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This object can be opened for writing or appending. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''x''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|This object can be executed (or mmap'd with PROT_EXEC into a task). |}
{| style="border-collapse:collapse;border-bottom:3px solid #999;" cellpadding="3px" width=100% |-style="background:#666;color:white;" ! width=60px style="border:1px solid gray;" |Mode ! style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:left;" |Meaning |- |+ Object Auditing Flags | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''A''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Audit successful appends to this object. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''C''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Audit the creation of the file/directory. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''D''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Audit the deletion of the file/directory. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''F''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Audit successful finds of this object. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''I''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Audit successful ACL inherits of this object. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''L''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Audit link creation. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''M''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Audit the setuid/setgid creation/modification. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''R''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Audit successful reads to this object. |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''W''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Audit successful writes to this object. |-style="background:lightgrey;" | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''X''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Audit successful execs of this object. |}
{| style="border-collapse:collapse;border-bottom:3px solid #999;" cellpadding="3px" width=100% |-style="background:#666;color:white;" ! width=60px style="border:1px solid gray;" |Mode ! style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:left;" |Meaning |- |+ Other Object Flags |- | style="border:1px solid gray;text-align:center;"|'''s''' | style="border:1px solid gray;"|Logs will be suppressed for denied access to this object. |}
