==R.L,C Components== Below is the summary of the three components R , L , and C :{| class="wikitable" width=100% ! Components!! Symbol !! Voltage V!! Current I!! Reactance X!! Impedance Z |- | Resistor || R || V = IR || I = <math>\frac{V}{R}</math>|| 0 || Z = R |- | Capacitor || C || V = <math>\frac{1}{C} \int I dt</math> || I = <math>C \frac{dV}{dt}</math> ||X = <math>\frac{1}{\omega C}/_-90 = </math><math>\frac{1}{j \omega C}</math> = <math>\frac{1}{sC}</math> || <math>Z = R + X = R + \frac{1}{j\omega C}</math> |- | Inductor || L || V = L <math>\frac{dI}{dt}</math> || I = <math>\frac{1}{L} \int V dt</math> || X = ωL/_90 = jωL = sL || <math>Z = R + X = R + j\omega L</math> |- |}
